        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Aug 1. 78<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S Morais<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I delayed so far<lb/> forwarding you my ad&#45;<lb/>dress as there was no<lb/> immediate hurry&#45;&#45;<lb/> We have had some very hot<lb/> weather here the greater part<lb/> of July it is now somewhat<lb/> abating&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Our city is remarkably quiet<lb/> I did not see your report<lb/> altho&#39; I have been told it<lb/> was satisfactory&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>In Lynchburg Virginia they<lb/> are about to consecrate a<lb/> Synagogue they invited Dr<lb/> Wise to officiate and he referred them<lb/> to me.  If they invite me<lb/> I shall go&#59; the consecration<lb/> is somewhere about the end<lb/> of this month.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>When the book arrives<lb/> please forward to<lb/> 162 Plum St<lb/> I suppose like us here<lb/> you are taking it as<lb/> quietly as possible<lb/> in this hot spell<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> Hoping you &#38; yours<lb/> are well<lb/></p>
            <p>I am<lb/>
                Yours obedty<lb/>
                A Harris<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
